children.text: Sore throat is very common in children. Most of the time, it’s nothing to worry about.
Get emergency medical care if your child has a sore throat and also:
⦁ Is drooling or has difficulty swallowing
⦁ White patches or pus on the back of the throat
⦁ Swollen lymph nodes in the neck
⦁ Signs of dehydration, such as no wet diapers or urine production 'in eight hours, dry skin, dry mouth, or crying without tears
Find possible causes of sore throat based on specific factors.
Viruses that cause the common cold and flu (influenza) also cause most sore throats. Less often, bacterial infections cause sore throats.
Viral illnesses that cause a sore throat include:
⦁ Common cold most common caused by rhinoviruses
If Sore throat in child is interfering with your daily life, log on AITMED and talk to a doctor to receive a treatment plan customized for you.
